    "recap_headline": "University of St. Thomas Athletics",
    "recap_text": "TULSA, OKLA.-\nThe St. Thomas\u00a0Tommies\u00a0fall to the Oral Roberts Golden Eagles 11-3 in Sunday's series finale.\nTanner Recchio\nled the offense with two hits, one of which was a solo home run, his first of the season.\nScoring Summary:\nThe\u00a0Tommies\u00a0struck first plating a run\u00a0in\u00a0the top of the first inning.\nAdam Puder\nreached on a walk and came around to score on an RBI single from\nOwen Bond\n, giving the Purple\u00a0a\u00a0early 1-0 lead.\nOral Roberts responded by plating one run of their own\u00a0in\u00a0the bottom of the\u00a0first, knotting the game at one.\u00a0The Golden Eagles then plated\u00a0six in the bottom\u00a0second, four of which came via a\u00a0grand\u00a0slam.\nSt. Thomas\u00a0plated their second run of the game in the third when\nMatthew Maulik\n's\u00a0sacrifice fly scored\nEaston Fritcher\nfrom third.\u00a0The Golden Eagles then responded by plating one of their own in the bottom of the\u00a0third,\u00a0making\u00a0the score 8-2.\nTanner Recchio\nthen hit a solo home run in the fifth for the\u00a0Tommies\u00a0third run of the game.\u00a0Oral Roberts responded by scoring\u00a0three in the home half of the inning, taking an 11-3 lead.\nUp Next\nThe\u00a0Tommies\u00a0will be back in Minnesota to take on the Golden Gophers across the river at Siebert Field Wednesday, March 25th. St. Thomas will then play their first home series of the season March 27-29 against Omaha.\nFollow Along:\nAny and all information\u00a0pertaining to\u00a0the St. Thomas baseball team can be found at tommiesports.com and on Twitter @TommieBase and Instagram at @TommieBaseball.",
    "watch_url": "https://www.midcosportsplus.com/"
  },
